reviews.text: Great food, great service, never have to wait for food and rarely missing ordered item. Love this place!! The quality of the food is really good and fresh!!
A decent Chinese restaurant mainly serving Shanghai style Chinese food. Good service and environment. Not very expensive if considering the district.
Food quality is ok, but the price is on the higher side. Coupled with the poor quality of service, it is going to take a long while before my next visit.

Food taste ok but portions are really tiny.  Ordered "Crystal Pork" and it was charged HK$72 plus service charge for 4 slices. If you charge premium price then I would expect more from you. Definitely not value for money.
Good food, good service, average 150 per head for lunch.

result.name: Tai Yau Plaza

reviews.text: Small shopping mall with several storeys.  Aisles were clean and not narrow.  There were restaurants, cafe and shops.  Washroom were acceptable.

It is a large shopping mall with boutiques, restaurants, optical shops and fashion stores. It's a four or five storey shopping center. In the past, this place was very quiet. But it is very lively now and has a lot of visitors. They love to stay in coffee shops for coffee. There are Pacific Coffee and Delifrance. 
On the ground floor of the mall, there was an oil painting exhibition. Previously, the quality of these works was not very good. However, as seen, the quality has improved. These paintings are up to a very high standard and worth watching.
Clean, quiet, good place for chitchat with friends at the coffee shop or noodle house.
Nice little hiding place for afternoon tea.

Wan Chai is at the dawn of a new era as the District’s most massive urban renewal projects to date are currently underway. Once completed, the District will become more than a vital link between Central and Causeway Bay; a new frontier of twenty first century’s metropolitan business and living. Physically located in the middle of Wan Chai and strategically located in the heart of these exciting prospects; the new Tai Yau Plaza is the place to be for retailers and shoppers alike.
